1 AN ACT relating to the Board of Nursing.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 314.121 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The Governor shall appoint a Board of Nursing consisting of seventeen (17)
5 members:
6 (a) Three (3) members shall be registered nurses actively engaged in clinical
7 practice consisting of direct bedside patient care on a daily basis and
8 licensed to practice in the Commonwealth at the time of appointment and
9 throughout their terms.
10 1. One (1) member shall be[,] selected from a list of names submitted by
11 the Kentucky School Nurses Association.
12 2. Two (2) members shall be selected from a list of names submitted by
13 the Kentucky Hospital Association;
14 (b) Three (3) members shall be advanced practice registered nurses actively
15 engaged in clinical practice and licensed to practice in the Commonwealth at
16 the time of appointment and throughout their terms, two (2) of whom shall
17 be selected from a list of names submitted by the Kentucky Association of
18 Nurse Practitioners and Nurse Midwives, and one (1) of whom shall be a
19 certified nurse anesthetist selected from a list of names submitted by the
20 Kentucky Association of Nurse Anesthetists;
21 (c) Two (2) members shall be practical nurses actively engaged in clinical
22 practice and licensed to practice in the Commonwealth at the time of
23 appointment and throughout their terms, selected from a list of names
24 submitted by the Kentucky Association of Licensed Practical Nurses;
25 (d) One (1) member shall be a nurse service administrator actively engaged in
26 practice who is a registered nurse licensed to practice in the Commonwealth
27 at the time of appointment and throughout the member's term, selected from
