1 a list of names submitted by the Kentucky Organization of Nurse Leaders;
2 (e) Four (4) members shall be actively engaged in nursing education, each of
3 whom is a registered nurse licensed to practice in the Commonwealth at the
4 time of appointment and throughout their terms,[ three (3) of whom shall
5 be] selected from a list of names submitted by the Kentucky League for
6 Nursing[ and one (1) of whom shall be selected from a list of names submitted
7 by the Kentucky Nurses Association];
8 (f) Two (2) members shall be registered nurses experienced in long-term care at
9 the time of appointment and throughout their terms, one (1) of whom shall
10 be selected from a list of names submitted by LeadingAge Kentucky, and one
11 (1) of whom shall be selected from a list of names submitted by the Kentucky
12 Association of Health Care Facilities; and
13 (g) Two (2) members shall be citizens at large, who are not associated with or
14 financially interested in the practice or business regulated.
15 (2) Each appointment shall be subject to confirmation by the Senate and shall be for a
16 term of four (4) years expiring on June 30 of the fourth year, except in 2024, when
17 new appointments shall be made by the Governor after July 15, 2024. A board
18 member shall not serve for more than three (3) consecutive terms, and shall be
19 ineligible for reappointment until the passage of one (1) full four (4) year
20 appointment cycle.
21 (3) (a) By August 1, 2024, the Kentucky School Nurses Association shall submit to
22 the Governor two (2) names of qualified individuals for appointment as a
23 registered nurse (R.N.) who are actively engaged in clinical nursing practice,
24 from which the Governor shall make an appointment as necessary by October
25 1, 2024. Thereafter, by March 1 of the year in which the term of an R.N.
26 actively engaged in clinical practice expires:
27 1. For one (1) of the three (3) members, the Kentucky School Nurses
