1 (i)[(j)] By March 1 of the year in which the certified registered nurse anesthetist
2 term expires, the Kentucky Association of Nurse Anesthetists shall submit to
3 the Governor two (2) names of qualified individuals who are actively engaged
4 in clinical nursing practice for the appointment, from which the Governor
5 shall make the appointment as necessary by July 1.
6 (j)[(k)] By August 1, 2024, the Kentucky Association of Nurse Practitioners and
7 Nurse-Midwives shall submit to the Governor the names of qualified
8 individuals for appointments of two (2) advanced practice registered nurses.
9 The appointed individuals shall be certified in different population foci and
10 shall be actively engaged in advanced nursing clinical practice. Two (2)
11 names of qualified individuals shall be submitted to the Governor for each
12 position. The Governor shall appoint one (1) advanced practice registered
13 nurse from the two (2) names submitted in one (1) population focus for an
14 initial term of four (4) years and shall also appoint one (1) advanced practice
15 registered nurse from the two (2) names submitted in another population focus
16 for an initial term of two (2) years. The Governor shall make each
17 appointment as necessary by October 1, 2024. Successive terms for each
18 advanced registered nurse practitioner shall be four (4) years. The two (2)
19 advanced practice registered nurses shall be certified in a different population
20 focus. Thereafter, on March 1 of the year in which the term of an advanced
21 practice registered nurse expires, the Kentucky Association of Nurse
22 Practitioners and Nurse-Midwives shall submit to the Governor the names of
23 two (2) qualified individuals, from which the Governor shall make the
24 appointment as necessary by July 1.
25 (k)[(l)] The Governor shall appoint two (2) members who shall be citizens at
26 large, who are not associated with or financially interested in the practice or
27 business regulated. The Governor shall make the appointments by July 1 of
