1 the year in which the citizen members' terms expire.
2 (4) Among the seventeen (17) members of the board, at all times, at least two (2)
3 members shall be appointed from each of the six (6) congressional districts of the
4 Commonwealth.
5 (5) Among the nurse board members appointed under subsection (1) of this section, no
6 less than three (3) and no more than six (6) nurse board members shall be nurse
7 educators. All other nurse members of the board shall be practicing nurses.
8 (6) A vacancy on the board shall be filled by the Governor as provided for under
9 subsection (1) of this section.
10 (7) The Governor may remove any member from the board for neglect of duty,
11 incompetence, or unprofessional or dishonorable conduct.
12 (8) Each R.N. member of the board shall be a citizen of the United States, a resident of
13 Kentucky, a graduate of an approved school of nursing, and a registered nurse in
14 this state. All shall have had at least five (5) years of experience in nursing, three
15 (3) of which shall immediately precede such appointment. Three (3) members shall
16 be engaged in clinical nursing practice; four (4) shall be engaged in nursing
17 education; three (3) shall be engaged in advanced practice registered nursing, one
18 (1) of whom shall be a certified registered nurse anesthetist; two (2) shall be
19 experienced in long-term care; and one (1) shall be in nursing administration.
20 (9) Each L.P.N. member of the board shall be a citizen of the United States, a resident
21 of Kentucky, a graduate of an approved school of practical nursing or its equivalent,
22 licensed as a licensed practical nurse in this state, have at least five (5) years of
23 experience in nursing, three (3) of which shall immediately precede this
24 appointment, and be currently engaged in nursing practice. Two (2) members shall
25 be engaged in clinical nurse practice.
